The bundled rules reference used to ground the AI Dungeon Master's narration
(the `src/main/resources/srd/srd-5.2.1.json` file: spells, monsters, magic
items, equipment, conditions, rules glossary, classes, species, feats, and
backgrounds) is derived from the SRD 5.2.1. It is generated from the official
SRD 5.2.1 PDF by `tools/extract-srd.py`. Monster entries are reduced to
behavioural lore — their numeric stat blocks (Armor Class, Hit Points, ability
scores, to-hit bonuses, damage, and Challenge Rating) are intentionally omitted
so the lore cannot contradict the game engine's authoritative combat math. These
adaptations are likewise made available under CC-BY-4.0.

